      "venue_constraint": "Current StrategyLab downloader is Binance public spot; use Binance symbols unless a new data adapter is added."
    },
    "causal_story": "For the intraday version, completed higher-timeframe context bars define the directional bias, execution-timeframe external market structure defines the active dealing range, and execution-timeframe internal market structure confirms entry timing inside that range. On BTCUSDT 15m, the engine resamples completed 15m candles into 1h context bars before accepting a 15m external BOS or CHoCH. After that external range creates an impulsive move and leaves imbalance, price must retrace into the correct premium/discount side near the 67 percent Fibonacci entry and fair value gap, sweep local liquidity, and then print an aligned internal BOS or CHoCH before entry. The stop remains anchored to the execution-range invalidation point and the target remains the opposing range extreme, preserving the set-and-forget risk model.",
    "timeframe_context_note": "The strategy is not one flat parameter set across all timeframes. Intraday/day-trading and swing-trading use different Fibonacci depths and structure roles. The current active research target is BTCUSDT 15m, but the parent preserves explicit profiles for 5m, 15m, and 4H/swing variants.",
    "timeframe_translation_components": [
      "15m intraday uses external structure for active dealing range and internal structure for execution timing",
      "5m intraday is treated as faster execution and should usually use a higher context timeframe",
      "4H swing mode uses a deeper Fibonacci retracement around 71 percent and does not necessarily require the same fast internal confirmation behavior",
      "profile-specific defaults must be tested as separate baselines, not blended into one optimized parameter soup"
    ],
    "direct_translation_components": [
      "external structure defines the active dealing range and directional context",
      "internal structure confirms intraday execution timing",
      "premium/discount midpoint filter",
      "67 percent intraday Fibonacci retracement for 5m-15m execution",
      "FVG/imbalance confluence",
      "liquidity sweep before entry",
      "internal BOS or CHoCH after retracement as execution confirmation",
      "set-and-forget stop at range invalidation and target at opposing range extreme"
    ],
    "transparent_approximations": [
      "external swings are confirmed symmetric pivots with a slower pivot period",
      "internal swings are confirmed symmetric pivots with a faster pivot period",
      "external structure is used for context and range construction",
      "internal structure is used for execution confirmation after retracement and sweep",
      "liquidity purge is approximated as a rolling-low/high stop sweep with close back inside",
      "imbalance is approximated as a three-candle fair value gap with ATR-normalized minimum size",
      "limit entry fills use deterministic OHLC intrabar rules, not order-book proof"
    ],
    "implementation_integrity_requirements": [
      "Use confirmed pivots only after pivot_right bars have closed.",
      "Do not use repainting values or future FVG information.",
      "If stop and target are both reachable on the entry/exit bar, use same_bar_exit_policy default stop_first.",
      "Emit diagnostic counters for every blocked setup and every exit reason."
    ]
